{
    "id": "c7f92eb45e",
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The prognostic value of lysine-specific demethylase 1 (LSD1) overexpression in various cancers has been investigated by many studies with inconsistent results. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "A meta-analysis was performed to assess the association between LSD1 and overall survival (OS) in cancer patients. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "Eligible studies were identified by searching the online databases PubMed and China National Knowledge Infrastructure up to February 2015. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "Hazard ratios (HRs) with 95% confidence intervals (CIs) were calculated to clarify the correlation between LSD1 expression and prognosis of different cancers. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "In total, nine studies with 1,149 cancer patients were included for final analysis. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "The meta-analysis suggested that LSD1 overexpression was associated with poor OS in cancer patients (HR =1.80, 95% CI: 1.39-2.34, P=0.000). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "Subgroup analysis by ethnicity, cancer type and HR estimate also showed that high levels of LSD1 were significantly correlated with OS. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        },
        {
            "text": "The meta-analysis showed that LSD1 overexpression may be associated with a worse prognosis in cancer patients.",
            "paragraph_rank": 0,
            "section_rank": 0
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Introduction",
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Lysine-specific demethylase 1 (LSD1) was the first characterized histone demethylase, which could specifically remove the methyl groups from mono-and dimethylated lysine (Lys)4 of histone H3 (H3K4me1/2) and Lys9 of histone H3 (H3K9me1/2). ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "1 LSD1 is essential for mammalian development and is involved in many biological processes, including cell type differentiation, gene activation, and gene repression. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "2 A recent study indicated that LSD1 might promote cell phase transition (deficiency in LSD1 led to partial cell cycle arrest in G 2 /M) and cell proliferation, suggesting that its overexpression might promote tumorigenesis. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "3 The expression of LSD1 has been associated with tumor recurrence during therapy in various cancers, further implicating LSD1 as a tumor promoter. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 1,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "4,5 Many studies investigated the prognostic value of LSD1 in various cancers. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "4,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 2,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Some studies found that the upregulation of LSD1 was associated with worse outcome in cancer patients. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "[6][7][8][9][10][11] However, some other studies showed insignificant or opposite result. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 3,
                    "end": 6,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "[7]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 6,
                    "end": 9,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 9,
                    "end": 12,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 12,
                    "end": 16,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 16,
                    "end": 20,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[12][13][14] Therefore, the relation between LSD1 expression and patient survival across different cancers remains controversial. ",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 4,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b11",
                    "text": "[12]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 4,
                    "end": 8,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b12",
                    "text": "[13]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 8,
                    "end": 12,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b13",
                    "text": "[14]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "To overcome the limitations of the single study, this meta-analysis was carried out with the aim of evaluating the relationship between LSD1 expression and prognosis of cancer patients.",
            "section": "Introduction",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Materials and methods",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "literature search and selection criteria demethylase 1\", \"tumor\", \"cancer\", \"neoplasm\", \"carcinoma\", \"malignant\", \"survival\", \"prognosis\", and \"prognostic\". ",
            "section": "Materials and methods",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The citation lists associated with the studies were used to identify additional eligible studies. ",
            "section": "Materials and methods",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The reviews and bibliographies were also manually inspected to find related articles.",
            "section": "Materials and methods",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The studies were included in our meta-analysis if they met the following inclusion criteria: ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "1) LSD1 expression evaluated in the human tissues; ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "2) tumors should be confirmed by pathological or histological examinations; ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "3) evaluation of the relationship between LSD1 expression and survival; ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "4) sufficient information provided to estimate the hazard ratios (HRs) with their 95% confidence intervals (CIs) for overall survival (OS). ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The exclusion criteria were as follows: ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "1) letters, case reports, reviews, and conference abstracts without original data; ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "2) articles from which the relevant data could not be extracted. ",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Of the studies which had duplicate data, only the most complete study was included in the analysis.",
            "section": "inclusion and exclusion criteria",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "Data extraction",
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "Data were evaluated and extracted independently from the eligible studies by two investigators (LXH and JW) under the guidelines of a critical review checklist of the Dutch Cochrane Centre proposed by Meta-analysis of Observational Studies in Epidemiology. ",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "15 The following items were recorded: first author's name, year of publication, ethnicity, method, tumor type, total number of patients, and HRs with their 95% CIs for OS. ",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b14",
                    "text": "15"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "If available, we calculated HRs with their 95% CIs using the data of observed deaths/cancer recurrences, the data of samples in each group, or the data provided by the authors. ",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "16 If not, the HRs with their 95% CIs and P-values were collected from the original article. ",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b16",
                    "text": "16"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "If only Kaplan-Meier curves were available, data were extracted from graphical survival plots to extrapolate HRs with their 95% CIs using previously described methods. ",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4
        },
        {
            "text": "17,18 Disagreements were resolved by discussion among all authors.",
            "section": "Data extraction",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 4,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b17",
                    "text": "17,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 3,
                    "end": 5,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b18",
                    "text": "18"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "statistical analysis",
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "HRs with their 95% CIs were calculated on the basis of the association between LSD1 expression and the OS of cancer patients. ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "The \u03c7 2 test and the I 2 statistic were used to evaluate the heterogeneity among studies. ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "19 If the heterogeneity was significant between studies (I 2 .50% or P,0.10), the random effects model was used; otherwise, the fixed effects model was used. ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "19"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "20 Sensitivity analysis was also conducted by sequential omission of individual studies to evaluate stability of the results. ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "text": "20"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Publication bias was estimated by Egger's linear regression test with a funnel plot. ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5
        },
        {
            "text": "21 The statistical analyses were performed using STATA version 12.0 software (Stata Corporation, Collage Station, TX, USA). ",
            "section": "statistical analysis",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 5,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 2,
                    "type": "bibr",
