        {
            "text": "The main results of this meta-analysis are listed in Table 2. ",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 7,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 53,
                    "end": 60,
                    "type": "table",
                    "ref_id": "tab_1",
                    "text": "Table 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Our analysis suggested that LSD1 overexpression was associated with poor OS in cancer patients (HR =1.80, 95% CI: 1.39-2.34, P=0.000) with heterogeneity (I 2 =53.6%, P=0.028) ( Figure 2).",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 7,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 177,
                    "end": 185,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "ref_id": "fig_1",
                    "text": "Figure 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "To explain the heterogeneity in OS, subgroup analysis was performed by ethnicity, cancer type, and HR estimate. ",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "Subgroup analysis by ethnicity suggested a significant association in Asian patients (HR =1.97, 95% CI: 1.61-2.41, P=0.000). ",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "When grouped according to cancer type, a significant relationship between LSD1 expression and OS was observed in esophageal cancer patients (HR =1.77, 95% CI: 1.34-2.33, P=0.000). ",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "When stratifying by HR estimate, significant relevance was observed both in \"reported directly from articles\" subgroup (HR =1.63, 95% CI: 1.17-2.29, P=0.004) and \"survival curves\" subgroup (HR =2.20, 95% CI: 1.63-2.96, P=0.000).",
            "section": "study characteristics",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 7
        },
        {
            "text": "sensitivity analysis and publication bias",
            "section_rank": 8
        },
        {
            "text": "Sensitivity analysis indicated that the pooled HRs were not significantly influenced by omitting any single study (Figure 3). ",
            "section": "sensitivity analysis and publication bias",
            "paragraph_rank": 9,
            "section_rank": 8,
            "ref_spans": [
